According to The Nation, fear has gripped police operatives attached to Achala Division in Anambra State over alleged persistent coughing of a newly posted Divisional Crime Officer (DCO). It was gathered that the DCO, who was posted to the division two weeks ago, has been coughing, raising suspicion that he may have caught the coronavirus. A signal from police command headquarters has been sent mandating the officer to subject himself to a test, it was learnt. The Nation gathered that the signal which came from the police command headquarters followed agitations by junior officers and men at the division who feared they may be at risk should the DCO have the virus. Source  It has been revealed that the 12 suspects currently being interrogated by Police operatives in Kwara State over the recent bank robbery in Offa were arrested through the tracking of mobile phones the robbers collected from victims. Vanguard gathered that after the robbery operation, the suspects took away the handsets… April 23, 2018 In "Top Stories" •The late Superintendent Amawu Gabriel Anang By JACOB KUBEKA, Abuja Five police officers attached to the Obudu Divisional Police Office in Cross River State, have been accused of extra-judicial killing and unlawful shooting of Superintendent Amawu Gabriel Anang on March 10, 2020. Ironically, the deceased, prior to his gruesome murder,… April 30, 2020 In "Metro" Abuja (Sundiata Post) Senior Special Assistant to Governor Willie Obiano of Anambra State, Mr Randie Chima, has been found dead in his room on the Nwakpodulu Avenue, Awka, the Anambra State capital     According to Punch,  the governor’s aide was last seen on Friday evening “hale and hearty”.  … August 13, 2018 In "News"